Subject: [PATCH] Detect unistd on non-Windows Bazel builds

The registry overlay does not run zlib's configure step and leaves
HAVE_UNISTD_H unset. That makes zlib call lseek without its prototype and use
long long instead of off_t, which produces conflicting Wasm signatures at
link time. Non-Windows Bazel toolchains provide unistd.h, so declare it just as
the configure build would.

diff --git a/BUILD.bazel b/BUILD.bazel
--- a/BUILD.bazel
+++ b/BUILD.bazel
@@ -111,7 +111,7 @@ cc_library(
     }),
     includes = ["zlib/include/"],
     local_defines = select({
         "@platforms//os:windows": ["_CRT_NONSTDC_NO_WARNINGS"],
-        "//conditions:default": [],
+        "//conditions:default": ["HAVE_UNISTD_H=1"],
     }),
     visibility = ["//visibility:public"],
 )
